## 1. Find my Holmes config

Look for whichever of these applies to my setup:

- **Helm**: my override values file (commonly `values.yaml`, `holmes-values.yaml`,
  or `values.override.yaml`) plus the upstream chart at `helm/holmes/values.yaml`
  if I have it checked out. Relevant keys:
  - `additionalEnvVars` ŌĆö API keys (`OPENAI_API_KEY`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`,
    `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`, `AZURE_API_KEY`, ŌĆ”) should come from a `secretKeyRef`,
    not be hard-coded.
  - `modelList` ŌĆö every model alias must map to a real provider model and
    include the provider prefix (`openrouter/openai/gpt-4.1`,
    `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929`, etc.).
- **Docker / docker-compose**: env vars on the `holmes` service.
- **CLI**: `~/.holmes/config.yaml` and shell env (`OPENAI_API_KEY`, `MODEL`,
  `CLASSIFIER_MODEL`, ŌĆ”).
{%- if deployment == "robusta_saas" %}
- **Robusta SaaS** (this is my case): I likely *can't* fix this myself because
  the LLM key is managed on Robusta's side. Confirm that's the case, and if so
  tell me to contact `support@robusta.dev` and stop. Only continue if you find
  config I actually own.
{%- endif %}

## 2. Verify what the running pod actually sees

```
kubectl exec -n <namespace> deploy/holmes -- printenv \
  | grep -iE 'API_KEY|API_BASE|MODEL|CLASSIFIER'
```

And check the Secret has the value you expect (no trailing whitespace, no
accidental quotes, not stale):

```
kubectl get secret <secret-name> -n <namespace> -o json \
  | jq '.data | map_values(@base64d)'
```

## 3. Map the error to a cause before proposing a fix

- `401` / `User not found` / `Invalid API key` ŌåÆ key missing, malformed,
  revoked, or the provider account is closed. Rotate the key in the provider
  dashboard and update the Secret.
- `404` / `model not found` ŌåÆ `modelList` alias points at a model name the
  provider doesn't expose, or the provider prefix is missing.
- `429` ŌåÆ rate limit / quota ŌĆö check the provider dashboard.
- `402` / `payment required` / `insufficient credits` ŌåÆ top up at the provider.
- `litellm.BadRequestError ... LLM Provider NOT provided` ŌåÆ `modelList` entry
  is missing the `<provider>/...` prefix.
{%- if provider == "openrouter" or "openrouter" in error_message|lower or "openrouter" in (model or "")|lower %}
- **OpenRouter-specific:** Holmes' default classifier model is not available
  on OpenRouter. `CLASSIFIER_MODEL` must also be set to an OpenRouter model
  (e.g. `openrouter/openai/gpt-4.1`). Confirm both `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` and
  `CLASSIFIER_MODEL` are present.
{%- endif %}

## 4. Propose the fix

Give me:
1. A concrete diff against my values file (or `kubectl edit secret` patch).
2. The `helm upgrade` command (or equivalent) to roll it out.
3. A one-line `kubectl` command I can run afterwards to confirm the fix took.

Use `valueFrom.secretKeyRef` for any credential ŌĆö never inline a key in
`values.yaml`.

